<% title "Organize a Ruby Event" %>
<% set_meta_tags description: "Start your own Ruby event. Whether it's a casual meetup at a bar or a full conference, the community needs more gatherings. Find guides, resources, and inspiration.",
     keywords: "organize ruby event, start ruby meetup, ruby conference organizer, ruby community, run a meetup",
     og: {title: "Organize a Ruby Event | RubyEvents.org", description: "Start your own Ruby event. Whether it's a casual meetup at a bar or a full conference, the community needs more gatherings. Find guides, resources, and inspiration."},
     twitter: {title: "Organize a Ruby Event | RubyEvents.org", description: "Start your own Ruby event. Whether it's a casual meetup at a bar or a full conference, the community needs more gatherings."} %>

<main>
  <div class="container">
    <section class="py-12 text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-primary mb-4">Organize a Ruby Event</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-600">
        Every great community event started with someone deciding to bring people together.
        That someone could be you. The Ruby community is built by people who show up
        and people who create spaces for others to show up.
      </p>
    </section>

    <div class="flex flex-col gap-12">
      <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">It's Simpler Than You Think</h2>
        <div class="prose prose-lg text-gray-600">
          <p>
            When people hear "organize an event," they often picture months of planning, sponsors,
            venues, and logistics. But it doesn't have to be that way.
          </p>
          <p>
            Some of the most impactful Ruby gatherings are simple: a table at a restaurant,
            a few people with laptops at a coffee shop, or drinks at a bar after work.
            No slides required. No sponsors needed. Just Rubyists talking about Ruby.
          </p>
          <p>
            If there's no Ruby meetup in your city, <strong>you</strong> can be the one to start it.
            Post on social media, invite a few colleagues, pick a date and a place. That's it.
            Then <%= link_to "add it to RubyEvents", "https://github.com/rubyevents/rubyevents/blob/main/docs/ADDING_EVENTS.md", target: "_blank", rel: "noopener noreferrer", class: "link link-primary" %>
            so other Rubyists in your area can find it.
            You'd be surprised how many people are waiting for someone to take the first step.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Event Format Ideas</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-500 mb-6">Not every event needs a stage and a projector. Here are some formats that work great.</p>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
          <div class="p-6 rounded-2xl bg-white border border-base-300">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-primary/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-3">
              <%= fa("utensils", size: :lg, class: "fill-primary") %>
            </div>
            <h3 class="font-bold mb-2">Dinner Meetup</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">Reserve a table at a restaurant, pick a topic, and invite local Rubyists. Great food and great conversations, no setup required.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="p-6 rounded-2xl bg-white border border-base-300">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-primary/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-3">
              <%= fa("beer-mug-empty", size: :lg, class: "fill-primary") %>
            </div>
            <h3 class="font-bold mb-2">Pub Night</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">The most casual format. Meet at a bar, chat about code (or not), and build friendships. Zero pressure, maximum fun.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="p-6 rounded-2xl bg-white border border-base-300">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-primary/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-3">
              <%= fa("laptop-code", size: :lg, class: "fill-primary") %>
            </div>
            <h3 class="font-bold mb-2">Hack Night</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">Bring laptops, pick an open source project or a coding challenge, and hack together. Pair programming welcome. Coffee shop or co-working space works perfectly.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="p-6 rounded-2xl bg-white border border-base-300">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-primary/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-3">
              <%= fa("bolt", size: :lg, class: "fill-primary") %>
            </div>
            <h3 class="font-bold mb-2">Lightning Talks</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">5-minute talks on any topic. Low pressure for speakers, high variety for attendees. A great way to encourage first-time speakers in your community.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="p-6 rounded-2xl bg-white border border-base-300">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-primary/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-3">
              <%= fa("book-open", size: :lg, class: "fill-primary") %>
            </div>
            <h3 class="font-bold mb-2">Study Group</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">Pick a book, a gem, or a Ruby feature. Read a chapter each week and discuss it together. Works great for learning and building deeper connections.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="p-6 rounded-2xl bg-white border border-base-300">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-primary/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-3">
              <%= fa("building-columns", size: :lg, class: "fill-primary") %>
            </div>
            <h3 class="font-bold mb-2">Conference</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">The big one. Multi-day, multiple tracks, sponsors, and a CFP. Start small. A single-day, single-track event is a great first step before scaling up.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="rounded-2xl border-2 border-primary/20 bg-primary/5 p-8 text-center">
        <div class="w-16 h-16 rounded-full bg-primary/10 flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-4">
          <%= fa("book", size: :xl, class: "fill-primary") %>
        </div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">The RubyEvents Organizer Guide</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 max-w-xl mx-auto">
          We're working on a comprehensive guide covering everything from finding a venue
          to managing speakers, handling sponsors, and building a community around your event.
        </p>
        <span class="badge badge-primary badge-lg">Coming Soon</span>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Resources for Organizers</h2>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <%= link_to "https://evilmartians.com/chronicles/lets-have-more-tech-meetups-a-quick-start-guide-to-holding-your-own", target: "_blank", rel: "noopener noreferrer", class: "flex items-center gap-3 p-4 rounded-xl border border-base-300 bg-white hover:border-primary hover:shadow transition-all" do %>
            <%= fa("newspaper", size: :lg, class: "fill-primary shrink-0") %>
            <div>
              <div class="font-semibold">A quick-start guide to holding your own meetup</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">Practical tips for starting a tech meetup by Evil Martians</div>
            </div>
          <% end %>

          <%= link_to "https://rubyconferenceproject.com/interviews/", target: "_blank", rel: "noopener noreferrer", class: "flex items-center gap-3 p-4 rounded-xl border border-base-300 bg-white hover:border-primary hover:shadow transition-all" do %>
            <%= fa("lightbulb", size: :lg, class: "fill-primary shrink-0") %>
            <div>
              <div class="font-semibold">Conference Organizing Insights</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">Interviews and tips from Ruby conference organizers</div>
            </div>
          <% end %>

          <%= link_to events_path, class: "flex items-center gap-3 p-4 rounded-xl border border-base-300 bg-white hover:border-primary hover:shadow transition-all" do %>
            <%= fa("calendar", size: :lg, class: "fill-primary shrink-0") %>
            <div>
              <div class="font-semibold">Browse existing events</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">See how other Ruby events are structured</div>
            </div>
          <% end %>

          <%= link_to continents_path, class: "flex items-center gap-3 p-4 rounded-xl border border-base-300 bg-white hover:border-primary hover:shadow transition-all" do %>
            <%= fa("globe", size: :lg, class: "fill-primary shrink-0") %>
            <div>
              <div class="font-semibold">Events worldwide</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">See where Ruby events are happening, and where they're not yet</div>
            </div>
          <% end %>

          <%= link_to "https://join.slack.com/t/rubycentralcommunity/shared_invite/zt-41jguxsjq-imDu9pZ0zbNVe5ermzPskA", target: "_blank", rel: "noopener noreferrer", class: "flex items-center gap-3 p-4 rounded-xl border border-base-300 bg-white hover:border-primary hover:shadow transition-all" do %>
            <%= fa("comments", size: :lg, class: "fill-primary shrink-0") %>
            <div>
              <div class="font-semibold">#meetup-organizers on Slack</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">Join the Ruby Central Community Slack for advice, regular calls, and support from fellow organizers</div>
            </div>
          <% end %>

          <%= link_to "https://rubycentral.org", target: "_blank", rel: "noopener noreferrer", class: "flex items-center gap-3 p-4 rounded-xl border border-base-300 bg-white hover:border-primary hover:shadow transition-all" do %>
            <%= fa("gem", size: :lg, class: "fill-primary shrink-0") %>
            <div>
              <div class="font-semibold">Ruby Central</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">The organization behind RubyConf and RailsConf</div>
            </div>
          <% end %>
        </div>
      </section>

      <%= render "page/community_cta", exclude: :organize %>
    </div>
  </div>
</main>
